setUp().details: Sets up the test environment before each test. Deploys mock EAS and AttestationTracker contracts with proper configuration.

testFuzz_ActiveStatusToggling(uint8,bool.details: Fuzz test for active status toggling with attestations. This ensures that active status changes don't affect attestation counts.

testFuzz_AttestationCounting(uint8).details: Fuzz test for attestation counting. This tests the attestation counter with various numbers of attestations.

test_AttestByDelegation_EmitsEvent().details: Test attestation wrapper emits event. This ensures proper event emission for off-chain tracking.

test_AttestByDelegation_MultipleAttestat.details: Test multiple attestations increment counter correctly. This verifies that the attestation counter properly increments with each attestation.

test_AttestByDelegation_Success().details: Test successful attestation through wrapper. This tests the core attestation wrapper functionality that forwards to EAS while incrementing the local attestation counter.

test_AttestByDelegation_WithValue().details: Test attestation with ETH value forwarding. This ensures that ETH sent with attestations is properly forwarded to EAS.

test_BitManipulation_ActiveStatusAndAtte.details: Test that active status and attestation count work independently. This is crucial for testing the DualStakingToken pattern's bit manipulation.

test_Constructor_Success().details: Test successful constructor with valid parameters. Verifies that initial state is properly set up.

test_EdgeCase_AttestationCounterOverflow.details: Test attestation counter overflow protection. This tests what happens when we try to increment past the maximum.

test_EdgeCase_MaxAttestationCount().details: Test maximum attestation counter (near 2^255-1). This tests the edge case of the bit manipulation pattern.

test_Gas_AttestByDelegation().details: Test gas usage for attestation operations. This helps ensure the contract is gas efficient.

test_GetMultisigInfo_Efficiency().details: Test the combined getter function for gas efficiency. This tests getMultisigInfo which returns both values in a single call.

test_IndependentMultisigs_AttestationTra.details: Test that different multisigs have independent attestation tracking. This ensures that each multisig's attestations and status are tracked separately.

test_RevertWhen_Constructor_ZeroEAS().details: Test that constructor rejects zero EAS address. This ensures the contract cannot be deployed with an invalid EAS address.

test_RevertWhen_SetMultisigActiveStatus_.details: Test that only owner can set active status. This ensures proper access control for administrative functions.

test_SetMultisigActiveStatus_AsOwner().details: Test setting multisig active status as owner. This tests the core active status toggle functionality.
